Preheat oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C). In a large skillet, saute chicken until browned. Remove from skillet and set aside. In same skillet, saute eggplant slices until slightly browned. Place sauteed chicken and eggplant in a lightly greased 9x13 inch baking dish. Top with tomato and onion slices, then sprinkle with dill weed, turmeric and salt to taste. Bake at 375 degrees F (190 degrees C) for 45 minutes or until chicken is cooked through and juices run clear.